theorem Topology.interior_inter_closure_compl_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior A ∩ closure (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxInt, hxClos⟩
    rcases hxInt with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUSub⟩
    have hNon : ((U ∩ Aᶜ) : Set X).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClos U hUopen hxU
    rcases hNon with ⟨y, ⟨hyU, hyComp⟩⟩
    have hyA : y ∈ A := hUSub hyU
    have hContr : False := hyComp hyA
    exact False.elim hContr
  · exact Set.empty_subset _

theorem Topology.interior_inter_interior_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ interior B) = interior A ∩ interior B := by
  -- First, show the left-hand side is contained in the right-hand side.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    have hx₁ : x ∈ interior A := by
      have hSub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A := fun y hy => hy.1
      exact interior_mono hSub hx
    have hx₂ : x ∈ interior B := by
      have hSub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ interior B := fun y hy => hy.2
      exact interior_mono hSub hx
    exact And.intro hx₁ hx₂
  · rintro x ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
    -- Consider the open set `interior A ∩ interior B`.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (interior A ∩ interior B) :=
      isOpen_interior.inter isOpen_interior
    have hSub : (interior A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ interior B := by
      intro y hy
      exact And.intro (interior_subset hy.1) hy.2
    -- By maximality of the interior, this open set is contained in
    -- `interior (A ∩ interior B)`.
    have hIncl :
        (interior A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∩ interior B) :=
      interior_maximal hSub hOpen
    -- Since `x` belongs to the open set, it also belongs to the interior.
    have hxIn : x ∈ interior A ∩ interior B := And.intro hxA hxB
    exact hIncl hxIn

theorem Topology.P3_of_open_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsOpen (closure A) → Topology.P3 (A := A) := by
  intro hOpen
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  have hxClos : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
  simpa [hOpen.interior_eq] using hxClos
